157struct nvkm_device_func {
158 struct nvkm_device_pci *(*pci)(struct nvkm_device *);
159 struct nvkm_device_tegra *(*tegra)(struct nvkm_device *);

161 int (*preinit)(struct nvkm_device *);
162 int (*init)(struct nvkm_device *);
163 void (*fini)(struct nvkm_device *, bool suspend);
164#ifdef __NetBSD__
165 bus_dma_tag_t (*dma_tag)(struct nvkm_device *);
166 bus_space_tag_t (*resource_tag)(struct nvkm_device *, unsigned bar);
167#endif
168 resource_size_t (*resource_addr)(struct nvkm_device *, unsigned bar);
169 resource_size_t (*resource_size)(struct nvkm_device *, unsigned bar);
170 bool cpu_coherent;
171};

231/* privileged register interface accessor macros */
232#ifdef __NetBSD__
233static inline uint8_t
234nvkm_rd08(struct nvkm_device *d, bus_size_t a)
235{
236 return bus_space_read_1(d->mmiot, d->mmioh, a);
237}
238static inline uint16_t
239nvkm_rd16(struct nvkm_device *d, bus_size_t a)
240{
241 return bus_space_read_stream_2(d->mmiot, d->mmioh, a);
242}
243static inline uint32_t
244nvkm_rd32(struct nvkm_device *d, bus_size_t a)
245{
246 return bus_space_read_stream_4(d->mmiot, d->mmioh, a);
247}
248static inline void
249nvkm_wr08(struct nvkm_device *d, bus_size_t a, uint8_t v)
250{
251 bus_space_write_1(d->mmiot, d->mmioh, a, v);
252}
253static inline void
254nvkm_wr16(struct nvkm_device *d, bus_size_t a, uint16_t v)
255{
256 bus_space_write_stream_2(d->mmiot, d->mmioh, a, v);
257}
258static inline void
259nvkm_wr32(struct nvkm_device *d, bus_size_t a, uint32_t v)
260{
261 bus_space_write_stream_4(d->mmiot, d->mmioh, a, v);
262}
263#else
264#define nvkm_rd08(d,a) ioread8((d)->pri + (a))
265#define nvkm_rd16(d,a) ioread16_native((d)->pri + (a))
266#define nvkm_rd32(d,a) ioread32_native((d)->pri + (a))
267#define nvkm_wr08(d,a,v) iowrite8((v), (d)->pri + (a))
268#define nvkm_wr16(d,a,v) iowrite16_native((v), (d)->pri + (a))
269#define nvkm_wr32(d,a,v) iowrite32_native((v), (d)->pri + (a))
270#endif
271#define nvkm_mask(d,a,m,v) ({ \
272 struct nvkm_device *_device = (d); \
273 u32 _addr = (a), _temp = nvkm_rd32(_device, _addr); \
274 nvkm_wr32(_device, _addr, (_temp & ~(m)) | (v)); \
275 _temp; \
276})

288/* device logging */
289#define nvdev_printk_(d,l,p,f,a...) do { \
290 struct nvkm_device *_device = (d); \
291 if (_device->debug >= (l)) \
292 dev_##p(_device->dev, f, ##a); \
293} while(0)
294#define nvdev_printk(d,l,p,f,a...) nvdev_printk_((d), NV_DBG_##l, p, f, ##a)
295#define nvdev_fatal(d,f,a...) nvdev_printk((d), FATAL, crit, f, ##a)
296#define nvdev_error(d,f,a...) nvdev_printk((d), ERROR, err, f, ##a)
297#define nvdev_warn(d,f,a...) nvdev_printk((d), WARN, notice, f, ##a)
298#define nvdev_info(d,f,a...) nvdev_printk((d), INFO, info, f, ##a)
299#define nvdev_debug(d,f,a...) nvdev_printk((d), DEBUG, info, f, ##a)
300#define nvdev_trace(d,f,a...) nvdev_printk((d), TRACE, info, f, ##a)
301#define nvdev_spam(d,f,a...) nvdev_printk((d), SPAM, dbg, f, ##a)
302#endif
